# THIS FILE LIST THE NLM RULES FOR WHOPE PROJECT. IT AIMS TO BE AN EASILY SCALABLE, HUMAN READABLE, PARSEABLE FILE.
# LINES STARTING WITH A "#" ARE COMMENTS AND THUS WILL NOT BE PARSED.
# THE FORMAT FOR DESCRIBING A RULE IS THE FOLLOWING:
# <ID>: IF TOPIC IS  <TOPIC> AND EMOTION IS <EMOTION> AND HISTORY IS [...<ID>] THEN <PROMPT>
# <ID> IS AN UNIQUE IDENTIFIER FOR THE RULE. FOR MAINTAINABILITY PURPOSES, INTEGER NATURAL ORDER IS PREFERRED
# <TOPIC> IS THE TOPIC THAT THE USER IS TALKING ABOUT. IT IS ONE OF THE FOLLOWINGS: SOCIETY, HEALTH, EDUCATION, BUSINESS, FAMILY, POLITICS
# <EMOTION> IS THE EMOTION THAT THE USER IS FEELING. IT IS ONE OF THE FOLLOWINGS: EMPTY, SADNESS, ENTHUSIASM, NEUTRAL, WORRY, SURPRISE, LOVE, FUN, HATE, HAPPINESS, BOREDOM, RELIEF, ANGER
# <HISTORY> IS A LIST OF RULES THAT HAVE BEEN USED BEFORE. IT IS A LIST OF ID'S SEPARATED BY COMMAS, INSIDE SQUARE BRACKETS, LIKE [1, 2, 3]
# <TOPIC>, <EMOTION> AND <HISTORY> SUPPORT THE USE OF THE BOOLEAN OPERATORS "NOT" AND "OR"
# <TOPIC> AND <EMOTION> SUPPORT THE USE OF THE BOOLEAN OPERATOR "AND"
# <PROMPT> IS THE PROMPT THAT WILL BE PASSED TO THE LLM
######################################################################
# 1: IF TOPIC IS BUSINESS AND EDUCATION AND EMOTION IS SADNESS OR WORRY AND HISTORY IS [] THEN ASK THE USER ABOUT THEIR CONCERNS ABOUT THE FUTURE
# 2: IF TOPIC IS FAMILY AND EMOTION IS HATE OR ANGER AND HISTORY IS [1] THEN ASK THE USER ABOUT THEIR RELATIONSHIP WITH THEIR FAMILY
# 3: IF TOPIC IS FAMILY AND EMOTION IS SADNESS AND WORRY OR NOT HAPPINESS AND HISTORY IS [1, 2] OR [1] THEN ASK THE USER ABOUT WHAT CONCERS THEM ABOUT THEIR FAMILY
4: IF TOPIC IS HEALTH AND EMOTION IS SADNESS AND HISTORY IS [] THEN ASK THE USER ABOUT THEIR HEALTH
